  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p>At the start of a combat encounter, if you are aware of your foes and aren't attempting to @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.Item.VMozDqMMuK5kpoX4]{Sneak} or @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.Item.XMcnh4cSI32tljXa]{Hide}, you can roll Intimidation for your initiative and can use the result to @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.Item.2u915NdUyQan6uKF]{Demoralize} one foe within range.</p><p>Additionally, if you have the @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.feats-srd.Item.ePObIpaJDgDb9CQj]{Battle Cry} feat, you can Demoralize up to two creatures within 60 feet of you who you're aware of.</p>"
